habitat_description: The highly fossorial Ringed salamanders utilize hardwood and mixed-pine hardwood forest within the Ozark Plateau and Ouachita Mountains (Petranka 1988, Dowling 1956). Typical breeding habitat includes temporary pools, farm ponds, or seasonally ephermal ponds within and immediately adjacent to forest (Brussock and Brown 1982, McMillian and Wilkinson 1972, Peterson et al. 1991, Spotila and Beumer 1970, Trapp 1956).
